# Strict Execution Order

| Rule | Enforcement |
| ---- | ----------- |
| Step 1 (Memory) is mandatory | Complete Step 1 before any other work. |
| Step 2 (Knowledge spine) default-required | Run Step 2 after Step 1 unless user explicitly skips KB spine. |
| Step 3 depends on Step 2 outcome | Start Step 3 only after Step 1 complete and Step 2 completed or explicitly skipped/recorded. |
| Order is fixed | Always `Step 1 -> Step 2 -> Step 3`. |

## Skip Handling

1. Refuse Step 1 skip requests.
2. Step 2 can be skipped only with explicit user request.
3. Record Step 2 skip as memory `decision`.
